---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '28 March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How AStar Development collects, uses, and protects your data in accordance with UK GDPR."
>
  <div class="privacy-container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <section aria-labelledby="what-we-collect">
      <h2 id="what-we-collect">What data we collect</h2>
      <p>
        When you use the contact form on this website, we collect the following
        information you provide:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name</li>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>The content of your message</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not collect any data beyond what you voluntarily submit through the
        contact form. We do not collect payment information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="how-it-is-used">
      <h2 id="how-it-is-used">How it is used</h2>
      <p>
        The information you provide through the contact form is used solely to
        respond to your enquiry. We do not sell, rent, or share your personal
        data with third parties for marketing purposes.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you opt in to receiving a copy of your message, your email address is
        used to send that copy via our email service provider (SendGrid, operated
        by Twilio). SendGrid processes your data as a data processor on our behalf.
        Their privacy policy is available at
        <a
          href="https://www.twilio.com/en-us/legal/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >twilio.com/en-us/legal/privacy<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="cookies">
      <h2 id="cookies">Cookies</h2>
      <p>This website uses two types of storage in your browser:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Theme preference</strong> — stored in <code>localStorage</code>
          under the key <code>theme</code>. This is a functional preference (it
          controls the visual appearance of the site) and does not require consent
          under UK GDPR. It is never transmitted to the server.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookie consent preference</strong> — stored in
          <code>localStorage</code> under the key <code>cookie-consent</code>.
          This records whether you have accepted or declined analytics cookies so
          the banner is not shown on every visit.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — only set if you accept analytics
          via the consent banner. See the Analytics section below.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use advertising cookies, tracking pixels, or any third-party
        marketing cookies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="analytics">
      <h2 id="analytics">Analytics (Azure Application Insights)</h2>
      <p>
        If you accept analytics via the cookie consent banner, this website uses
        Azure Application Insights (operated by Microsoft) to collect anonymised
        usage data including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
        <li>General geographic region (country / city, not precise location)</li>
        <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
        <li>Referrer URL</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        IP addresses are anonymised before storage. This data is used to
        understand how the site is being used and to improve it. Microsoft&rsquo;s
        privacy policy is available at
        <a
          href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-gb/privacystatement"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >privacy.microsoft.com<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you decline analytics, Application Insights is not initialised and no
        analytics data is collected during your visit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="your-rights">
      <h2 id="your-rights">Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
      <p>Under UK data protection law, you have the following rights:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — you may request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — you may ask us to correct inaccurate data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> — you may ask us to delete your personal data where there is no legitimate reason for us to continue holding it.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — you may request that we provide your data in a commonly used, machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — you may object to our processing of your personal data in certain circumstances.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below.
        We will respond within one calendar month.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="data-retention">
      <h2 id="data-retention">Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Contact form submissions are retained for up to 12 months from the date
        of receipt, after which they are deleted. Analytics data is retained for
        90 days in Azure Application Insights.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="contact-data">
      <h2 id="contact-data">Contact for data requests</h2>
      <p>
        For any data-related requests or questions about this privacy policy,
        please use the contact form on this website at
        <a href="/contact">/contact</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are not satisfied with our response, you have the right to lodge a
        complaint with the UK Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office (ICO) at
        <a
          href="https://ico.org.uk"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >ico.org.uk<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 64px 24px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--text);
    transition: color 0.25s;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    transition: color 0.25s;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding-top: 8px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--section-border);
    transition: color 0.25s, border-color 0.25s;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    transition: color 0.25s;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 8px 0 12px 0;
    padding-left: 24px;
    color: var(--text);
    transition: color 0.25s;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  a:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.88em;
    background: var(--surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    transition: background-color 0.25s, border-color 0.25s;
  }

  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px;
    height: 1px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border-width: 0;
  }
</style>
